The paper discusses a method for identifying the most influential cited references in a given set of papers, which is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science such as digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), scientometrics (cs.SI), cybernetics (cs.CY), and software engineering (cs.SD). However, since the paper focuses on analyzing citation patterns and impact sequences rather than developing new algorithms or models, it is less likely to belong to sub-fields such as computer vision (cs.CV) or machine learning (cs.LG).
